{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idef13ed37-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s1967"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1967"},"text":"§ 1967.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Addition to Emergency Credit Revolving Fund of sums from liquidation of loans; authorization of appropriations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idef13ed38-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s1967/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" All sums received by the Secretary from the liquidation of loans made under the provisions of this subchapter or under the Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1949-04-06"},"text":"April 6, 1949","children":[],"tail":", as amended, or the Act of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1954-08-31"},"text":"August 31, 1954","children":[],"tail":", and from the liquidation of any other assets acquired with money from the Emergency Credit Revolving Fund shall be added to and become a part of such fund."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idef13ed39-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s1967/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" There are authorized to be appropriated to the Emergency Credit Revolving Fund such additional sums as the Congress shall from time to time determine to be necessary.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idef13ed3a-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/128/tIII/s327"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–128, title III, § 327","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1961-08-08"},"text":"Aug. 8, 1961","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/75/312"},"text":"75 Stat. 312","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idef13ed3b-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idef13ed3c-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idef13ed3d-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1949-04-06"},"text":"April 6, 1949","children":[],"tail":", as amended, referred to in subsec. (a), is "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-04-06/ch49"},"text":"act Apr. 6, 1949, ch. 49","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/43"},"text":"63 Stat. 43","children":[],"tail":", which was classified to sections 1148a–1 to 1148a–3 of Title 12, Banks and Banking, was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/128/s341/a"},"text":"section 341(a) of Pub. L. 87–128","children":[],"tail":", and is covered by this chapter."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1954-08-31"},"text":"August 31, 1954","children":[],"tail":", referred to in subsec. (a), is "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1954-08-31/ch1145"},"text":"act Aug. 31, 1954, ch. 1145","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/68/999"},"text":"68 Stat. 999","children":[],"tail":", which was classified as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1148a–1"},"text":"section 1148a–1 of Title 12","children":[],"tail":", was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/128/s341/a"},"text":"section 341(a) of Pub. L. 87–128","children":[],"tail":", and is covered by this chapter."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idef13ed3e-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Abolition of Emergency Credit Revolving Fund","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Emergency Credit Revolving Fund, referred to in this section and in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s1966"},"text":"section 1966 of this title","children":[],"tail":", was abolished and its assets and liabilities transferred to the Agricultural Credit Insurance Fund by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s1929"},"text":"section 1929 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
